Acute septicaemic Pasteurella multocida infection in an African grey parrot (Psittacus erithacus timneh) after a bite from a pet rat (Rattus norvegicus). P. multocida infections in man and birds as a sequel to animal bites are reviewed and a case report is presented of a fatal P. multocida septicaemia in a parrot after a bite from a pet rat. The need for immediate intravenous or intramuscular treatment of birds with a penicillin after bites from all mammals is stressed.